      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "07397a2e7473cd1e524c24d18774accf05adf8ad",
            "subject": "LU-13713 lnet: check rtr_nid is a gateway"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Wang Shilong",
          "email": "wshilong@ddn.com",
          "date": "2020-06-30 01:12:48.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2020-07-10 16:53:13.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-13729 osd-ldiskfs: race access to iam_formats during setup",
        "message": "LU-13729 osd-ldiskfs: race access to iam_formats during setup\n\nIt might be possible during OST mounting, two targets reach\niam_format_guess() at the same time, if @initialized is 0,\nthey both access iam_lxx_format_init(), however list operation\ninside is not protected by any locking which cause list corruptions\nfinally.\n\nWe could fix this by doing formats registration in module init,\nsince there are only two formats, just remove pointless list.\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Shilong <wshilong@ddn.com>\nChange-Id: I6dd5a4d1297792b47fb4b94052465a7e0f9123aa\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/39213\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: John L. Hammond <jhammond@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Yingjin Qian <qian@ddn.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
